    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The geometric correction of spatial distortions such as tilt and relief in aerial photographs, resulting in uniformity of scale. Orthocorrected images may be used to measure true distances; a basis of aerial photogrammetry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
